article.headline: Nicholls St. 87, Dillard 45
article.story: THIBODAUX, La. -- Ryan Bathie scored a game-high 19 points to lead four Nicholls State players in double figures as the Colonels beat Dillard 87-45 on Monday night. Anatoly Bose and Fred Hunter scored 13 apiece, and Justin Payne added 10 for the Colonels (6-3). Nicholls State shot 56.3 percent from the field (36 of 64) in a one-sided contest that the Colonels led 50-22 at halftime. Joshua Mitchell was the only Blue Devils (3-5) player to reach double figures in the contest, scoring 10 points. Mitchell was 2-for-3 from beyond the arc. The Blue Devils shot 36.8 percent (14 of 38) in the loss.
